1) Install react js and Tailwind css
- npm create vite@latest --> folder name "client" --> React --> JavaScript + SWC
- cd client --> npm install --> Now you can run the app

2) Search Tailwind css installation steps from --> https://tailwindcss.com/docs/guides/vite
- Install --> npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
- Initialize --> npx tailwindcss init -p
- Open tailwind.config.js  and change all the file in it with the new file from the tailwind website.
- Copy and paste the three lines of code form index.css (from the website) to the client file folder index.css
  src --> index.css --> 
                      @tailwind base;
                      @tailwind components;
                      @tailwind utilities;

3) Open MERN-Blog folder and Initialize git --> git init   (This enables to controll our progaram with git)
   Initialized empty Git repository in D:/REACT PROGRAMS/MERN-Blog/.git/
   - PS D:\REACT PROGRAMS\MERN-Blog> git add .
   - PS D:\REACT PROGRAMS\MERN-Blog> git commit -m "Install react js and tailwind css and create the first template"
   Now go to your github account and create a new repository.
   - Repository name: mern-blog
   - Description: Mern blog using tailwind css
   - Make it Public and Private
   - Finally --> Create Repository

   - After creating the repository it gives us the follwing code. Then, add in to MERN-Blog folder step by step
   - â€¦or push an existing repository from the command line

     PS D:\REACT PROGRAMS\MERN-Blog> git remote add origin https://github.com/kalkidan-elel/mern-blog.git
     PS D:\REACT PROGRAMS\MERN-Blog> git branch -M main
     PS D:\REACT PROGRAMS\MERN-Blog> git push -u origin main
  